review_blob: bottled Nov. 2001.  Really complex, flavors of nuts, berries, and chocolate in the malts.  Full body, the palate is very nice and warms the throat and stomach.  Some nice hops balance this beer off.
beer_name: Fish Tale Leviathan Barleywine - Barrel Aged

review_blob: This beer is awesome.  The malt is wonderful as it's full flavored, rich, and sweet.  The beer is warm, very pleasantly hopped, finishes very smoothly, with a nice lingering hop flavor.  Outstanding brew.
Pours wonderfully dark, with a very nice creamy head.  Very nutty, and a nice cream like palate, almost milky.  The oats really come out in the finish.  Probably my favorite by this brewer, thus far.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Barney Flats Oatmeal Stout

review_blob: roasted malt, nutty, some chocolate hints very much like a brown ale.  I think this one could probably add a little more.

Pours dark, aroma of fruit, and alcohol stand out
I think this is a great beer.  Very barlywine like.  Lots of fruit flavors on the palate, sweet, rich.  Full bodied, and full flavored.

Pours dark, with a light tan head.
Nicely done.  The flavors in this beer are very subtle, roasted malt, chocolate, even a bit of hops.

This beer is just a basic ale.  There really isn't anything fancy about it.  It certainly isn't robust.  There is alight hint of spruce on the palate, but after that, just a regular old ale.  Make this beer bigger please!
sweet, malty.  slightly spicey.  The palate, is light.  Not one of the better sam smith beers, I must say.

I like the subtleness of this porter.  The flavors are interesting.  Toasted malt, some hints of smoke, and cookie dough like flavors.  This isn't a beer to gulp, but a beer, to drink slowly and really think about the flavors.

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Good amber flavor.  Nice medium body, characterized by a pleasant maltiness, balanced by a floral hop finish.  Very drinkable, smooth, enjoyable.

This beer, is very interesting.  However I don't find it very bitter at all.  Maybe I have destroyed tastebuds.  It is sweet, and rather crisp.  There is some spice notes in the body as well which are enjoyable.

Pours deep black, and thick.  The aroma is complex.  With hints of vanilla, chocolate, and toffee.  The palate is nearly perfect.  Full, rich and dark.  Some sweet notes come through as well.  The beer finishes strongly with just the right amount of bitterness, and warms the stomach.

the smoke really comes through in a hickory complex.  the aroma is very smokey.  The palate is more mellow in comparison.  It compliments the ale quite nicely.  I don't find this beer to be over "smoked" at all.

This beer is awesome.  The aroma is lightly floral, with some citrus notes.  It pours a clear golden color, with a small cream head.  The palate is wonderful, It is soft, rich, somewhat buttery as well.  It is hopped just right.  It is fully bitter, and the finish is nice and dry.

The word that comes to mind is "fake".  The green bottle.  The "premium beer" bull shit on the label.  Don't buy it.  If you really have to drink a cheap beer, save a buck or two and drink bud.  Even better save lots of bucks, and drink water.

Awesome.  This beer distinguishes itself from other stouts, and other beers period.  It's not just the strong alcohol content.  It takes a few sips to "warm up" to the flavor,'  but it is well worth it.  The aroma sweet.  It pours a nice thick black color, no head however.  On the palate the beer is very complex.  It's very sweet, I get a definite sugar complex, caramel, hazelnuts and more more more.  This beer is great, and everyone should drink it.

Black in color, the head is a nice brown, which lasts.  The aroma is light, but I get a spicy sense from it.  Initially on the palate it's dark, and then follows with a nice sweetness.  Brown sugar is what comes to mind for me.  I also get hints of vanilla as well.  It is thick and creamy, a very nice stout.

Pours a nice dark color, with a dark brown head.  The aroma is light, but smells of nuts, and chocolate.  The flavor, is quite nutty, some caramel, and chocolate touches linger over the palate.  It finishes with a slightly hoppy touch.  I'd like to have a little more fullness of flavor, or something to differentiate it from other porters.
So malty.  The palate, is rich, somewhat sweet.  But the malt flavor is really the big thing.  It poors a dark color, with a nice brown head.  The flavors become darker, roasted, nicely done.
pours very clear, light amber, with a slight creamy head.  The palate is very dry.  It's bland, no real hops presence.  It's a cheap beer in a fancy bottle.  Don't waste your time.
A decent beer for this style, however I feel it lacks a lot of complexity.  It has a nice creamy quality, and a dry finish
extremely dark in color.  The aroma is very complex, vanilla, caramel come through.  The palate is a bit light for my taste, however the complexity of the dark malt is really wonderfull.
Pours a nice amber hue, small head.  aroma is nutty, and somewhat metallic.  Caramel, toffee, and a pleasant malt flavor come through on the palate, Theres a very slight hop presence, which is nice.
Very malty, and well balanced.  Havent had one quite like it, however its quite good.  The hops and malts make a nice play together for an interesting beer.

This is a very unique IPA.  The aroma is faintly floral, some sweet qualities come out as well.  It pours orange, with a nice white bubbly head.  Its initially sweet on the palate, and fades quickly.  This beer is very dry.  Id like to find some more hops on the palate.  If you find IPAs too bitter, you might be interested in trying this one.

Im not a big fan of fruit beers, but this one has some interesting qualities.  First off, if youve ever had rasberry creme soda, thats the first thing it makes me think of off the pour.  Its ruby, the head is almost pink.  The rasberries really come through in the aroma  Its sweet on the mouth, the rasberries add a pleasant creaminess.  That said Im still not convinced that fruit and beer go all that well together.  But I do reccomend trying this one.  It has to be one of the best fruit beers found in the states.
full aroma, of fruit, nuts, and some smoke.  The flavor is very dark, almost burnt tasting, I unfortunately was not a big fan of this one.

milennium edition;
Very much a pale ale.  Crisp, clear, and clean, well balanced, however it is extremely dry.  A little to dry for my tastes
clearn brown in color, nice cream head.  This beer is quite nutty, and malty.  The hops presence is nice, not very bittery at all, finishes gently.
Pours dark amber/ ruby in color.  The aroma is complex, with some fruit notes.  The flavor is full, malty and good.

dark brown in color, nice cream head that lasts.  Aroma, is nutty, slightly smokey and some fruit notes as well.  The flavor is complex, starts nutty, the middle has some sweet fruit like flavors, nice hop presence helps to finish great.
What more can be said about this beer, it"s simply awesome.  Dark, complex, strong, delicious

beer_brewer_name: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
review_blob: nice golden color, aroma is complex, hops, sugar, fruit flavors.  The palate is think, full and rich.  I love the hops on the finish, it"s quite bitter.

light amber in color, aroma is sweet, some malt, nutty, is nice with the floral hops  Initially hoppy, malt flavors linger over the palate, the hop finish diminishes slowly.  has a nice creamy character as well
pours brown, toasted nuts, sugar aroma  The flavor is full, dark with a nice bitter quality, however the palate was thin, too thin for this beer.
Interesting brew.  Pale, some nice spices on the palate.  Quite crisp, and nicely dry hopped on the finish.
Prety nice lager, clear golden in color, decent cream head.  Very dry, crisp, lightly hopped.  Quite sweet as well.
sweet, sugary.  Aroma comes through as nice fruit, which also comes through vaguley on the palate.  I just want more flavor from this one.  It has potential.

Deep red in color. small cream head.  Very nutty in aroma.  Starts rich, malty, with some nut flavors.  The hops are very well balanced, to add a pleasant bitterness.  More nut, toffee flavors on the finish.
Bitter Bitter Bitter.  Very citrus aroma, fully hopped.  Really makes me think IPA.  Decent beer, but not overly impressive.
beer_name: Fish Tale Organic Winterfish Seasonal Ale

review_blob: Awesome, what more can be said about it.  Full bodied, nice sweet aroma.  Rich and complex.  The flavors are dark, roasted malt, nice hop blend.  Warms you up as it goes down.  Awesome beer.
Wonderful Holiday ale. Deep brown color on the pour, aroma is light and sweet.  The flavor is rich, malty with some caramel touches.  Full Flavored, full bodied.  Really awesome brew.
beer_name: Maritime Pacific Jolly Roger Christmas Ale

review_blob:
Pours dark, with a  nice cream head. Nose is nutty, thick malt. 
Very nice, Malty, with nice coffee tones.  Almost porter like.  Rich, sweet, with a lightly bitter finish.

The thought that comes to mind to me is apple cider.  It smells like it, and tastes like it, with some nice bitterness.  It has a nice deep amber color, and a slight white head, that lasts for about half the glass.
nice deep amber color, cream head.  Quite malty, with a pleasant hop balance.  Some nice spices within the hops.  Not too bad at all.
2002, not pleased with this one.  It has a nice spicey aroma, it just doesnt carry over to the palate.  I found the palate to be somewhat weak, and flavorless.  Just give me more!
2002 edition.  Oh this is a fun one.  Very sprucey, and very bitter.  Thick dark beer, which is naturally thick and rich on the palate.  Well done
Aroma is spicy, chocolate, and apple.  Orange amber in color.  On the palate lightly roasted malt, wheat and caramel.  I was hoping for a little bit more from this one.
Aroma smells of spruce, dark amber in color.  spicy, thick palate, finishes very sprucy, and bitter.

Well I have to disagree with many of the comments below.  My beer was very nice, deep amber in color with a nice cream head.  The aroma was sweet fruit, malt and some nice spices.  The palate is nice and rich, quite spicy, and finishes with a very pleasant bitter finish.  Fine winter ale.
